THIRD-PARTY DATA
-----------------
HPOGraph compiles and ships a SQLite database (data/hpo.db.gz) built from
several independently maintained, third-party biomedical data sources.
These sources are NOT covered by the HPOGraph license above and remain
subject to their own respective terms:

  - Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO) -- ontology graph and disease-phenotype
    annotations (hp.json, phenotype.hpoa). Published by the HPO Consortium
    (https://hpo.jax.org) under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
    International License (CC BY 4.0). Attribution: Human Phenotype
    Ontology Consortium.

  - OMIM (Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man) -- disease identifiers and
    names surfaced via HPO's annotation files reference OMIM entries. OMIM
    data is subject to its own terms of use; see https://omim.org/help/agreement
    Users who wish to redistribute or build commercial products on top of
    OMIM-derived data must review and comply with OMIM's terms directly.

  - Orphanet (ORPHA identifiers) -- rare disease identifiers and names
    referenced via HPO's annotation files. See https://www.orphadata.com/
    for Orphanet's own data usage terms.

  - HGNC (HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee) -- approved gene symbols and
    metadata (hgnc_complete_set). See https://www.genenames.org for terms.

  - ClinGen (Clinical Genome Resource) -- gene-disease validity
    classifications and gene dosage sensitivity / clinical actionability
    curations (Gene-Disease Validity and Curation Activity summary
    reports). Published by ClinGen (https://clinicalgenome.org) under the
    CC0 1.0 Universal Public Domain Dedication. ClinGen requests attribution
    where practical: "The following curated content was obtained from the
    Clinical Genome Resource (www.clinicalgenome.org): Gene-Disease Validity
    classifications, Gene Dosage Sensitivity classifications, and Clinical
    Actionability scores." See https://clinicalgenome.org/docs/terms-of-use/
    for full terms. ClinGen keys its curations by Mondo Disease Ontology ID;
    HPOGraph attaches most of these to a specific candidate disease using
    the Mondo crosswalk below, falling back to gene-level matching only
    where no exact Mondo match is available for that disease.

  - Mondo Disease Ontology exact-match crosswalk -- mappings from Mondo IDs
    to OMIM and Orphanet identifiers (mondo_exactmatch_omim.sssom.tsv and
    the Orphanet subset of mondo.sssom.tsv), used solely to resolve which
    specific candidate disease a ClinGen curation applies to. Published by
    the Monarch Initiative (https://github.com/monarch-initiative/mondo)
    under CC BY 4.0; Mondo's dedicated OMIM exact-match mapping file is
    additionally released under CC0 1.0. Only identifier-to-identifier
    correspondences to OMIM/Orphanet are extracted and compiled here --
    HPOGraph does not use or ship any UMLS/MedGen-derived mappings from
    Mondo's full release, which carry separate, more restrictive terms.

It is the responsibility of any user or redistributor of HPOGraph's compiled
database to review and comply with the license terms of each underlying
data source listed above, independent of the HPOGraph license itself.

NOT A DIAGNOSTIC TOOL
-----------------------
HPOGraph is intended for research, education, and phenotype-exploration
purposes. It is not a standalone diagnostic tool, and its disease/gene
ranking output must be interpreted by a qualified clinical or genetics
professional -- it does not constitute a diagnosis or clinical
recommendation on its own.
